The **Digital Archiving Stores **service allows to create and manage Digital Archiving store resources, and provides an editor to configure their settings such as document categories and indexes, as well as Platform and Public access endpoints.

> Note

For more information, see: [Digital Archiving Store Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-store-resource-reference).

## **Accessing the Digital Archiving Stores service**
- Access the Doxee Platform home page.

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) on the navigation bar to expand the menu.

- Select **Digital Archiving Stores**.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

## Main screen
The **Digital Archiving Stores** main screen displays a list of all Digital Archiving store resources available to the current user for the selected account.

The main screen provides two views:

- **Recent**: Digital Archiving store resources that were recently viewed or edited by the current user![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

- **All**: All available Digital Archiving store resources

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Column**

**Description**

**Store**

Name of the Digital Archiving store resource

**Modified on**

Date and time when the Digital Archiving store was last modified

**Modified by**

Name of the user who last modified the Digital Archiving store

> Note

For more information, see: [Digital Archiving Store Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/digital-archiving-store-resource-reference)

For more information on how to manage resources, see: [Doxee Platform Repository User Manual](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-repository-user-manual)

### Navigation bar and common functionalities
> Note

For more information on the navigation bar and the common actions that can be performed on tables, see: 

- [Doxee Platform 3 NavigationBar](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-navigation-bar)

- [Doxee Platform 3 Common Functionalities](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-3-common-functionalities)

### **Creating a new Digital Archiving store**
- Click **New **in the main screen.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Select the **Folder **where the new Digital Archiving store resource will be saved.

> Note

For more information on folders, see: [Doxee Platform Repository User Manual](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-repository-user-manual).

- Enter an **Alias** for the new Digital Archiving Store resource.

- Click **Create**. The new Digital Archiving Store resource is opened in the editor. For example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Editor](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-editor)

> Tip

You may also create a Digital Archiving store resource from the **Repository **service. For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Repository User Manual](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-repository-user-manual) 

### Actions on Digital Archiving stores
- Move your mouse pointer over the row corresponding to a Digital Archiving store. The ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) **Edit **and ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**More**)  icons are displayed.

- Click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) (**More**) to expand the context menu and select the required action.

![](data:image/png;base64,) 

**Action**

**Description**

**Edit**

Open the Digital Archiving store in the editor.

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Digital Archiving Stores - Editor](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-digital-archiving-stores-editor)

> Tip

To edit a resource, you may also click ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)  (**Edit**) directly.

It is also possible to edit resources of type Digital Archiving store from the Doxee Platform Repository UI. For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Repository User Manual](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-repository-user-manual).

**Locate**

Locate the Digital Archiving store in the Doxee Platform Repository. This action will open a new browser tab displaying the selected resource in its corresponding location in the tree structure.

> Note

For more information on folders, see: [Doxee Platform Repository User Manual](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-repository-user-manual).
